        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12175",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi,\n\nThe reason why sslv2:\/\/ is used by default is because some servers (without naming any ;) have a really bad implementation of sslv3 and the connection is not properly closed - so a warning is thrown by PHP, despite the fact that the data is properly recieved. When using ssl:\/\/ these servers presumably negotiate sslv3:\/\/ but cause warnings to be thrown.\n\nI see no reason why there shouldn't be a configuration option to override the transport stream - I will look into it and try to add it as soon as I can.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-08T11:05:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-08T11:05:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12227",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is now fixed in r. 2759 - you can now do this:\n\n{code}\n$client = new Zend_Http_Client();\n$client->setUri(\"https:\/\/localhost\/info.php\");\n$client->setConfig(array(\n\t'ssltransport' => 'tls'\n));\n\n$response = $client->request('GET');\n{code}\n\nAs you can see, setting the 'ssltransport' config value will override the sslv2 stream transport layer. \n\nPlease do not close this bug yet - I will close it once I have documented this new feature. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-14T12:17:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-14T12:17:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12229",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Feature is now documented, bug is closed. ",
